            <div type="commentary"><p> N. Sharankov has revised the inscription and proposes restoration of the last verse of the epigram such as, e.g., εὐτε[χνίῃ κλεινὸς πᾶσιν ἐν] οἰνοπόλοις “famous for his skill among all bird-seers”, since the last word in the line is
ΟΙΝΟΠΟΛΟΙ, i.e. οἰνοπόλοις in the dative plural, and not in the genitive singular οἰνοπόλου, as read by Mihailov
